ne returns to the outdoor performance, where the same two performers jump together. One lifts or supports the other through a flip: the performer in the yellow cap bends backward across the partner’s body, legs swinging up and over in a controlled tumble while a rope turner at the side keeps an arm raised. Spectators behind them smile and lean forward to watch.\n\nThe two performers land and face each other again, laughing and clapping hands. The McDonald’s logo is visible on the back of one white vest, along with small printed words beneath it. Another young man in a red jacket and white pants steps into the routine. He faces the performer in the yellow cap, lifting his knees in rhythm while they mirror each other’s small hops and quick foot movements. The performer in earmuffs stands nearby, clapping along.\n\nThe action cuts to another close-up of the product: a golden Chicken McNugget is dipped into a small white plastic cup of sauce. The nugget goes down into the glossy sauce and rises coated; thick sauce stretches and drips back into the cup in a slow ribbon. Back outside, the performers continue jumping and leaning through the rope, with one man bent forward as if becoming part of the obstacle or stunt while another guides the movement behind him.\n\nA product display appears on a tabletop: stacked McDonald’s Chicken McNuggets boxes, including brown boxes with “Chicken McNuggets” printed on the sides and large numerals such as “20,” plus a light-colored clamshell box on top. Hands reach in from different sides and quickly take the packages away, leaving the tabletop almost empty.\n\nThe performers continue beside the restaurant windows. The young woman in the yellow cap and the young man in the red jacket face each other closely, gesturing with their hands as if playfully talking or counting beats. Then they resume bouncing footwork together, clapping palms and hopping in place. Another close-up again shows a Chicken McNugget being pulled open, the white interior steaming between the two golden halves.\n\nNear the end, the wider group returns to the center of the patio. Several performers tumble and slide into low poses while the crowd forms a semicircle around them. Large white on-screen text appears across the bottom: “IT’S A GOOD TIME FOR THE GREAT TASTE,” with the red McDonald’s arches logo at the lower right. Behind the dancers, a large yellow arch sign is visible near the restaurant entrance. The performers finish on the ground in a playful pile or seated cluster, smiling.\n\nThe final close view centers on the young woman in the yellow cap reclining comfortably among the other performers. She smiles directly forward, her red-and-white McDonald’s-colored top visible, while friends in red athletic jackets grin behind and beside her. She lifts one hand in a small approving gesture, ending the scene with a cheerful, relaxed expression.",
